      "content": "yeah i get that it's complicated, but i'm seeing a lot of data suggesting that when benefits go up, the incentive to take low-wage jobs just drops. like, if the math doesn't work out for a person to actually be better off working, why would they? dont you think the data shows a pretty clear link between higher welfare spending and people opting out of the workforce?",
